How about:
```suggestion
theorem derivedSeries_succ_eq_top_iff (n : ) :
    derivedSeries R L (n + 1) =   derivedSeries R L 1 =  := by
  simp only [derivedSeries_def]
  induction' n with n ih;  simp
  rw [derivedSeriesOfIdeal_succ]
  refine fun h  ?_, fun h  by rwa [ih.mpr h]
  rw [ ih, eq_top_iff]
  conv_lhs => rw [ h]
  exact LieSubmodule.lie_le_right _ _

theorem derivedSeries_eq_top (n : ) (h : derivedSeries R L 1 = ) :
    derivedSeries R L n =  := by
  cases n
   rfl
   rwa [derivedSeries_succ_eq_top_iff]
```

I think it is slightly more useful to prove:
```suggestion
theorem derivedSeries_lt_top_of_solvable [IsSolvable R L] [Nontrivial L] :
    derivedSeries R L 1 <  := by
```
since it is _slightly_ easier to pass from `I < J` to `I  J` using `LT.lt.ne` than vice-versa (when `J = `).

How about:
```suggestion
instance instCanLiftSubmoduleLieSubmodule : CanLift (Submodule R M) (LieSubmodule R L M) ()
```

Those are not syntactically equal, for some reason. And I think the `.toSubmodule` version provided by `()` has better simp properties.

We should probably fix the coe at some point.
